main event: On November 7, 1958, in El Paso, Texas, a yellowish-white, round object, the size of a dime, was observed at a 45-degree elevation in the east. The observation suggests it was probably a balloon.
interesting points: The object was described as yellowish-white, round, and the size of a dime.
The sighting was categorized as a Ground-Visual observation.
The object was visible for an unknown length of time and was observed by a civilian, 22 years old.
Despite the initial observation, the object was later believed to be Venus by the Senior Director on Duty
The Texas Highway Department reported the weather conditions as clear and calm.
